sources.data_found: Della GPU nodes include: 42 nodes × 8 H100 SXM (PLI) = 336 H100; 18 nodes × 8 H200 PCIe (AI Lab) = 144 H200; 59 nodes × 4 A100 80GB = 236 A100 80GB; 20 nodes × 2 A100 40GB = 40 A100 40GB; 10 nodes × 8 (A100 at 50% compute power, 40GB) = 80 'A100 40GB'; 2 nodes × 28 (MIG 10GB) = 56 MIG 10GB (not counted in requested fields). Visualization: della-vis1 has 1× A100 40GB; della-vis2 has 4× P100 16GB. GH200 note: one login node and one compute node with Grace Hopper Superchip.
Tiger: 12 GPU nodes × 4 H100 80GB = 48 H100 (form factor not stated); 1 GPU node × 8 H200 141GB = 8 H200; plus 40 CPU nodes with 1× L40S 48GB each = 40 L40S.
Stellar: 6 GPU nodes with 2 GPUs/node (A100 40GB) = 12 A100 40GB; and 1 GPU node with 8 A100 SXM 40GB = 8 A100 40GB; total Stellar A100 40GB = 20.

Adroit GPU nodes: 1 node × 4 A100 80GB = 4 A100 80GB; 1 node × 4 V100 32GB = 4 V100; plus visualization node adroit-vis has 2× A100 80GB = 2 A100 80GB. (Also 1 node × 8 A100 MIG 20GB exists but not counted in requested fields.)

Hardware Overview summarizes major clusters and confirms H100 SXM (PLI) nodes, H200 PCIe nodes, Tiger H100 and L40S nodes, and Stellar A100 GPU nodes; page notes that numbers may lag and recommends snodes/shownodes for most up-to-date details.

student_data.notes: Searched for Princeton CS enrollment counts specifically for AY 2024-2025 / Fall 2024. Princeton’s Office of Institutional Research 'Majors' page indicates an 'Undergraduate Degree Majors 2020-2021 through 2024-2025' dataset, but it is hosted on tableaupublic.princeton.edu and returns an 'Unexpected Error' page (no extractable 2024-2025 counts for Computer Science concentrators/majors). The Registrar’s 'University Enrollment Statistics' page similarly points to Tableau views that error. Princeton’s Common Data Set 2024-2025 (https://ir.princeton.edu/document/556) provides overall undergraduate/graduate headcounts as of Oct 15, 2024, but does NOT break enrollment down by Computer Science, nor by M.S.E. vs Ph.D. within CS. Because no working, explicitly dated (2024-2025 / Fall 2024) source with CS-specific enrollment counts was accessible, all counts are set to 0.

gpu_resources.notes:
Per-cluster arithmetic (nodes × GPUs_per_node):

Della (https://researchcomputing.princeton.edu/systems/della)
- H100 SXM: 42 × 8 = 336 (counted in h100_sxm_count)
- H200: 18 × 8 = 144 (counted in h200_count)
- A100 80GB: 59 × 4 = 236 (counted in a100_80gb_count)
- A100 40GB: (20 × 2) + (10 × 8) + (della-vis1: 1) = 40 + 80 + 1 = 121 (counted in a100_40gb_count)
- P100: (della-vis2: 4) = 4 (counted in p100_count)
- GH200: 1 login + 1 compute = 2 (counted in gh200_count)

Tiger (https://researchcomputing.princeton.edu/systems/tiger)
- H100 (assumed PCIe based on 4 GPUs/node typical for PCIe systems; form factor not explicitly stated): 12 × 4 = 48 (counted in h100_pcie_count)
- H200: 1 × 8 = 8 (counted in h200_count)
- L40S: 40 × 1 = 40 (counted in l40s_count)

Stellar (https://researchcomputing.princeton.edu/systems/stellar)
- A100 40GB: (6 × 2) + (1 × 8) = 12 + 8 = 20 (counted in a100_40gb_count)

Adroit (https://researchcomputing.princeton.edu/systems/adroit)
- A100 80GB: (1 × 4) + (adroit-vis: 2) = 4 + 2 = 6 (counted in a100_80gb_count)
- V100: 1 × 4 = 4 (counted in v100_count)

Totals across all clusters:
- h100_sxm_count = 336
- h100_pcie_count = 48
- h200_count = 144 + 8 = 152
- a100_80gb_count = 236 + 6 = 242
- a100_40gb_count = 121 + 20 = 141
- v100_count = 4
- p100_count = 4
- l40s_count = 40

Not counted in requested fields:
- Della MIG 10GB: 2 × 28 = 56 (10GB MIG slices)
- Adroit A100 MIG 20GB: 1 × 8 = 8 (20GB MIG slices)
